 A Sample BDD (Behavioral Driven Development using Python - Behave)

 We have to install python behave module as a pre-requisite.

 pip install behave
 ------------------

 References ::
 -------------

  - https://behave.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#feature-files

  - https://jenisys.github.io/behave.example/


Execution ::
------------

 - Goto Dir chapter1
 - Run as 

 	python -m behave features/ --no-capture

 	When we give flag as --no-capture - It will also print output to screen, if we have any print statement in our code,
 	it will get printed too.


